{
  "answer": "**Yājñavalkya Smṛti 2.135** lists potential heirs in sequence for a sonless man (as part of the broader rules on the division of inheritance in Chapter 2). It specifies: \"The wife, the daughters, the parents, the brothers, and likewise their sons, kinsmen of the same gotra, cognate relations, a pupil, and a fellow-student.\"[^1]\n\nThis verse continues into the next (2.136), which explains that \"in the absence of a preceding one, each succeeding one is the heir to the wealth.\"[^2]\n\n[^1]: Yājñavalkya Smṛti, Chapter 2, [p-807a82](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/02/translation/#p-807a82).\n[^2]: Yājñavalkya Smṛti, Chapter 2, [p-c8fbd0](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/02/translation/#p-c8fbd0).",
